claim.claim-text:
1. A method of estimating a sound speed, the method comprising:
transmitting an acoustic signal from a first location through a water column;
receiving a first scattered signal at a second location, the first scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by a scattering layer in the water column;
receiving a second scattered signal at a third location, the second scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by the scattering layer;
receiving a third scattered signal at a fourth location, the third scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by the scattering layer;
estimating a travel time based on at least one of the first, second, or third scattered signals;
generating a cross-correlation signal comprising a product of echoes of at least two of the first, second, and third scattered signals having an approximate bistatic geometry;
estimating a travel time difference based on at least the cross-correlation signal; and
estimating a sound speed based on the estimated travel time and the estimated travel time difference.

11. The method of claim 1, wherein estimating a travel time comprises:
determining a first time interval between i) a first time when the acoustic signal is transmitted and ii) a second time when the first scattered signal is received;
determining a second time interval between i) the first time and ii) a third time when the second scattered signal is received;
determining a third time interval between i) the first time and ii) a fourth time when the third scattered signal is received; and
averaging the first, second, and third time intervals to generate an estimate of travel time.

15. A method of estimating a sound speed profile, the method comprising:
transmitting a first acoustic signal from a first location towards a plurality of reflectors comprising at least a first scattering layer at a first depth in a water column and a second scattering layer at a second depth in the water column;
transmitting a second acoustic signal from a second location towards the plurality of reflectors;
receiving a first scattered signal at a third location from the plurality of reflectors, the first scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by the first and second scattering layers;
receiving a second scattered signal at a fourth location from the plurality of reflectors, the second scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by the first and second scattering layers;
estimating at least a first and second travel time based on at least one of the first or second scattered signals;
generating a cross-correlation signal comprising a cross-correlation of the first scattered signal and the second scattered signal having an approximate bistatic geometry;
estimating at least first and second travel time differences based on the cross-correlation signal;
estimating the first and second depths;
estimating a sound speed to the first and second depths; and
estimating a sound speed profile based on the estimated depths and estimated sound speeds.

19. A system for estimating a sound speed, the system comprising:
means for transmitting an acoustic signal through a water column from a first location;
means for receiving a first scattered signal at a second location, the first scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by a scattering layer in the water column;
means for receiving a second scattered signal at a third location, the second scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by the scattering layer;
means for receiving a third scattered signal at a fourth location, the third scattered signal comprising a plurality of echoes of the acoustic signal reflected by the scattering layer;
means for estimating a travel time based on at least one of the first, second, or third scattered signals;
means for generating a cross-correlation signal comprising a product of at least two of the first, second, and third scattered signals in accordance with the bistatic invariance principle;
means for estimating a travel time difference based on at least the cross-correlation signal; and
means for estimating a sound speed based on the estimated travel time and the estimated travel time difference.

20. A non-transitory computer-readable storage medium having instructions stored thereon which, when executed by a processor, causes a method of estimating a sound speed to be performed, the method comprising:
estimating a travel time based on at least one of a first scattered signal, a second scattered signal, or a third scattered signal, wherein each of the first, second, and third scattered signals comprises a plurality of echoes of an acoustic signal reflected by a scattering layer in a water column;
generating a cross-correlation signal comprising a product of a least two of the first, second, and third scattered signals in accordance with the bistatic invariance principle;
estimating a travel time difference based on at least the cross-correlation signal; and
estimating a sound speed based on the estimated travel time and the estimated travel time difference.
